label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, SW);
label("$D$", D, S);
[/asy]

Since $OB = OC,$ $\angle BOC = \frac{\pi}{2},$ so $\angle BAC = \frac{\pi}{2} - \angle BOC = \angle AOC.$  Therefore, triangle $AOC$ is isosceles, so $\angle OAC = \angle OCA.$  But $\angle BAC = 2 \angle D,$ so $\angle OAC = \angle D.$

Then $\angle AOC = 2 \angle OAC = 2 \angle D,$ so $\angle BOC = 2 \angle D.$  Hence, $\angle BAC = \frac{\pi}{2} - \angle BOC = \frac{\pi}{2} - \angle D.$  Therefore, $k = \frac{\pi}{2} - \angle D.$

